</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Default buffer size for the connection\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.defaultPayloadBytes","kind":"def","line":86,"name":"Std.Http.Config.defaultPayloadBytes","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Http/Server/Config.lean#L86-L86"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.maximumRecvSize\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">maximumRecvSize</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The maximum size that the connection can receive in a single recv call.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.maximumRecvSize","kind":"def","line":81,"name":"Std.Http.Config.maximumRecvSize","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Http/Server/Config.lean#L81-L81"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.enableKeepAlive\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">enableKeepAlive</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Whether to enable keep-alive connections by default.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.enableKeepAlive","kind":"def","line":76,"name":"Std.Http.Config.enableKeepAlive","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Http/Server/Config.lean#L76-L76"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.headerTimeout\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">headerTimeout</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Std/Time/Time/Unit/Millisecond.html#Std.Time.Millisecond.Offset\">Time.Millisecond.Offset</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Maximum time (in milliseconds) allowed to receive the complete request headers after the first\nbyte of a new request arrives. This prevents Slowloris-style attacks where a client sends bytes\nat a slow rate to hold a connection slot open without completing a request. Once a request starts,\neach individual read must complete within this window. Default: 5 seconds.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.headerTimeout","kind":"def","line":71,"name":"Std.Http.Config.headerTimeout","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Http/Server/Config.lean#L71-L71"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.keepAliveTimeout\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">keepAliveTimeout</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">{</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">:</a> <a href=\"./Std/Time/Time/Unit/Millisecond.html#Std.Time.Millisecond.Offset\">Time.Millisecond.Offset</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">//</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#GT.gt\">&gt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">}</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Timeout for keep-alive connections\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.keepAliveTimeout","kind":"def","line":63,"name":"Std.Http.Config.keepAliveTimeout","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Http/Server/Config.lean#L63-L63"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.lingeringTimeout\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">lingeringTimeout</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Std/Time/Time/Unit/Millisecond.html#Std.Time.Millisecond.Offset\">Time.Millisecond.Offset</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Timeout (in milliseconds) for receiving additional data while a request is actively being\nprocessed (e.g. reading the request body). Applies after the request headers have been parsed\nand replaces the keep-alive timeout for the duration of the request.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.lingeringTimeout","kind":"def","line":58,"name":"Std.Http.Config.lingeringTimeout","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Http/Server/Config.lean#L58-L58"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.maxHeaderBytes\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">maxHeaderBytes</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Maximum aggregate byte size of all header field lines in a single message\n(name + value bytes plus 4 bytes per line for `: ` and `\\r\\n`). Default: 64 KiB.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.maxHeaderBytes","kind":"def","line":51,"name":"Std.Http.Config.maxHeaderBytes","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Http/Server/Config.lean#L51-L51"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.maxHeaders\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">maxHeaders</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Maximum number of headers allowed per request.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.maxHeaders","kind":"def","line":45,"name":"Std.Http.Config.maxHeaders","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Http/Server/Config.lean#L45-L45"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.maxRequests\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">maxRequests</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Maximum number of requests per connection.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.maxRequests","kind":"def","line":40,"name":"Std.Http.Config.maxRequests","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Http/Server/Config.lean#L40-L40"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.maxConnections\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">maxConnections</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config\">Config</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Maximum number of simultaneous active connections (default: 1024).\nSetting this to `0` disables the limit entirely: the server will accept any number of\nconcurrent connections and no semaphore-based cap is enforced. Use with care — an\nunconstrained server may exhaust file descriptors or memory under adversarial load.\n","docLink":"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.maxConnections","kind":"def","line":35,"name":"Std.Http.Config.maxConnections","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Http/Server/Config.lean#L35-L35"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Http/Server/Config.html#Std.Http.Config.mk\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Http</span>.<span class=\"name\">Config</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> →\n  <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> →\n    <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> →\n      <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> →\n        <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Time/Time/Unit/Millisecond.html#Std.Time.Millisecond.Offset\">Std.Time.Millisecond.Offset</a> →\n          <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">{</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">:</a> <a href=\"./Std/Time/Time/Unit/Millisecond.html#Std.Time.Millisecond.Offset\">Std.Time.Millisecond.Offset</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">//</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#GT.gt\">&gt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">}</a> →\n            <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Time/Time/Unit/Millisecond.html#Std.Time.Millisecond.Offset\">Std.Time.Millisecond.Offset</a> →\n              <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bo